{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place milk, yeast and sugar in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl with oil.","Add oil, water, flour and salt then knead <nobr>4 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared bowl, cover with cling film then set aside to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Towards end of rising time, prepare topping."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Generously grease a large baking tray with oil.","Transfer risen dough to prepared baking tray. Use fingertips to spread dough out to the size of the tray, with a slightly thicker edge, then set aside.","Place oil, water and salt in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add onions then mix again <nobr>8 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Arrange onion mixture evenly over dough then set aside to rise for 30 minutes. Towards end of proving time, preheat oven to 200°C.","Bake for 25-30 minutes (200°C) until golden. Remove from oven and cool slightly, then serve cut in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["100 g milk","2 ½ tsp dried instant yeast","1 tsp sugar","50 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","200 g water","600 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for flouring","1 Tbsp fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["45 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","50 g water","2 tsp fine sea salt","250 g white onions, sliced (3 mm)"]}],"id":"r131893","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-LRB_QRjsI9Y\/XZWYT0tOawI\/AAAAAAAAd8A\/07zmqZbI8BgFCABvmZhNV0wTPSw40U6kQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6lsyiOpxfHMt-ptw.png","title":"Onion Focaccia","publishedAt":"2016-09-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12.9 g","fat":"17.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"80.7 g","calories":"2143 kJ \/ 512 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, large bowl, large baking tray, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Alternatively, roll dough out on a floured surface with a rolling pin then transfer to prepared baking tray.","To make a focaccia with tomatoes and herbs, replace the onions with cherry tomatoes and add herbs of choice to taste.<br>     <br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","3h 20m","6 portions"]}